HOUSE BILL 1094
J5 6lr2416
CF SB 910
By: Delegates Hutchinson and Adams
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Health
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Health Insurance – Graduate–Level Clinical Interns – Required Reimbursement
3 FOR the purpose of establishing that insureds and any other persons covered by certain
4 health insurance policies, contracts, or certificates are entitled to reimbursement for
5 the services rendered by a graduate–level counseling, social work, or psychology
6 clinical intern under certain circumstances; and generally relating to health
7 insurance reimbursement for the services of clinical interns.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
9 Article – Insurance
10 Section 15–704, 15–707, and 15–714
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2017 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Insurance
16 15–704.
17 (a) This section applies to each individual, group, or blanket health insurance
18 policy, contract, or certificate of an insurer or nonprofit health service plan that:
19 (1) (i) is delivered or issued for delivery in the State;
20 (ii) is issued to a group that is incorporated or has a main office in
21 the State; or
22 (iii) covers individuals who reside or work in the State; and
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
