2 HOUSE BILL 1094
1 (2) is issued, renewed, amended, or reissued on or after October 1, 2003.
2 (b) If a policy, contract, or certificate subject to this section provides for
3 reimbursement for a service that is within the lawful scope of practice of a licensed clinical
4 professional counselor, a licensed clinical marriage and family therapist, a licensed clinical
5 alcohol and drug counselor, or a licensed clinical professional art therapist, the insured or
6 any other person covered by the policy or certificate is entitled to reimbursement for the
7 service.
8 (C) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, IF A POLICY,
9 CONTRACT, OR CERTIFICATE SUBJECT TO THIS SECTION PROVIDES FOR
10 REIMBURSEMENT OF A SERVICE THAT IS WITHIN THE LAWFUL SCOPE OF PRACTICE
11 OF A LICENSED GRADUATE PROFESSIONAL COUNSELOR, THE INSURED OR ANY
12 OTHER PERSON COVERED BY THE POLICY, CONTRACT, OR CERTIFICATE IS ENTITLED
13 TO REIMBURSEMENT FOR THE SERVICE PROVIDED BY A GRADUATE–LEVEL
14 COUNSELING CLINICAL INTERN.
15 (2) THE SERVICES PROVIDED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE
16 REIMBURSABLE IF THE SERVICES ARE:
17 (I) PROVIDED AT AN OUTPATIENT HEALTH CARE FACILITY;
18 (II) PROVIDED BY A COUNSELING CLINICAL INTERN WHO IS:
19 1. ENROLLED IN A COUNSELING GRADUATE PROGRAM;
20 AND
21 2. PROVIDING THE SERVICES UNDER THE DIRECT
22 SUPERVISION OF A LICENSED CLINICAL PROFESSIONAL COUNSELOR; AND
23 (III) BILLED BY THE SUPERVISING LICENSED CLINICAL
24 PROFESSIONAL COUNSELOR.
25 15–707.
26 (a) This section applies to each individual, group, or blanket health insurance
27 policy of an insurer or nonprofit health service plan that:
28 (1) (i) is delivered or issued for delivery in the State;
29 (ii) is issued to a group that is incorporated or has a main office in
30 the State; or
31 (iii) covers individuals who reside or work in the State; and

HOUSE BILL 1094 3
1 (2) is issued, renewed, amended, or reissued on or after January 1, 1978.
2 (b) If a policy or certificate subject to this section provides for reimbursement for
3 a service that is within the lawful scope of practice of a licensed certified social worker, the
4 insured or any other person covered by the policy or certificate is entitled to reimbursement
5 for the service regardless of whether the service is performed by a physician or licensed
6 certified social worker–clinical.
7 (C) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, IF A POLICY
8 OR CERTIFICATE SUBJECT TO THIS SECTION PROVIDES FOR REIMBURSEMENT OF A
9 SERVICE THAT IS WITHIN THE LAWFUL SCOPE OF PRACTICE OF A LICENSED MASTER
10 SOCIAL WORKER, THE INSURED OR ANY OTHER PERSON COVERED BY THE POLICY,
11 CONTRACT, OR CERTIFICATE IS ENTITLED TO REIMBURSEMENT FOR THE SERVICE
12 PROVIDED BY A GRADUATE–LEVEL SOCIAL WORK CLINICAL INTERN.
13 (2) THE SERVICES PROVIDED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE
14 REIMBURSABLE IF THE SERVICES ARE:
15 (I) PROVIDED AT AN OUTPATIENT HEALTH CARE FACILITY;
16 (II) PROVIDED BY A SOCIAL WORK CLINICAL INTERN WHO IS:
17 1. ENROLLED IN A SOCIAL WORK GRADUATE PROGRAM;
18 AND
19 2. PROVIDING THE SERVICES UNDER THE DIRECT
20 SUPERVISION OF A LICENSED CERTIFIED SOCIAL WORKER–CLINICAL; AND
21 (III) BILLED BY THE SUPERVISING LICENSED CERTIFIED SOCIAL
22 WORKER–CLINICAL.
23 15–714.
24 (a) This section applies to each individual or group health insurance policy,
25 contract, or certificate that:
26 (1) (i) is issued or delivered in the State;
27 (ii) is issued to a group that is incorporated or has a main office in
28 the State; or
29 (iii) covers individuals who reside or work in the State; and
30 (2) is issued, renewed, amended, or reissued on or after July 1, 1972.

4 HOUSE BILL 1094
1 (b) Notwithstanding any other provision of a policy, contract, or certificate subject
2 to this section, if the policy, contract, or certificate provides for reimbursement for a service
3 that is within the lawful scope of practice of a licensed psychologist, the insured or any
4 other person covered by the policy, contract, or certificate is entitled to reimbursement for
5 the service regardless of whether the service is performed by a physician or licensed
6 psychologist.
7 (C) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, IF A POLICY,
8 CONTRACT, OR CERTIFICATE SUBJECT TO THIS SECTION PROVIDES FOR
9 REIMBURSEMENT OF A SERVICE THAT IS WITHIN THE LAWFUL SCOPE OF PRACTICE
10 OF A LICENSED PSYCHOLOGIST, THE INSURED OR ANY OTHER PERSON COVERED BY
11 THE POLICY, CONTRACT, OR CERTIFICATE IS ENTITLED TO REIMBURSEMENT FOR
12 THE SERVICE PROVIDED BY A GRADUATE–LEVEL PSYCHOLOGY CLINICAL INTERN.
13 (2) THE SERVICES PROVIDED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE
14 REIMBURSABLE IF THE SERVICES ARE:
15 (I) PROVIDED AT AN OUTPATIENT HEALTH CARE FACILITY;
16 (II) PROVIDED BY A PSYCHOLOGY CLINICAL INTERN WHO IS:
17 1. ENROLLED IN A PSYCHOLOGY GRADUATE PROGRAM;
18 AND
19 2. PROVIDING THE SERVICES UNDER THE DIRECT
20 SUPERVISION OF A LICENSED PSYCHOLOGIST; AND
21 (III) BILLED BY THE SUPERVISING LICENSED PSYCHOLOGIST.
22 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall apply to all
23 policies, contracts, and health benefit plans issued, delivered, or renewed in the State on or
24 after January 1, 2027.
25 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
26 January 1, 2027.

